  m_text: "<b><size=120%>Libraries & Algorithms</size></b>\n\n  <link=\"https://github.com/Cysharp/NativeCompressions\"><u><b>NativeCompressions</b></u></link>
    by Cysharp\n    License: MIT\n    Usage: High-performance native LZ4 bindings
    for Chunk Serialization.\n    Version: 0.6.0\n\n  <link=\"https://github.com/RelativityMC/ScalableLux\"><u><b>Starlight
    / ScalableLux</b></u></link> by RelativityMC\n    License: LGPL 3.0\n    Usage:
    Reference implementation for the BFS flood-fill lighting propagation and optimization
    details.\n\n  <b>FastNoiseLite</b> by Auburn\n    License: MIT\n    Usage: Burst-compatible
    port of the v1.1 C# version used for high-performance 'Standard\" terrain generation.\n   
    Version: 1.1\n    Notes: Burst port by Project Developer\n\n  <b>Perlin Noise</b>
    by Unity Technologies\n    License: Proprietary\n    Usage: Used via 'Mathf.PerlinNoise'
    for 'Legacy' world terrain generation.\n\n  <link=\"https://discussions.unity.com/t/how-to-generate-a-grid-from-the-center/171186/2\"><u><b>Spiral
    Loop</b></u></link> by Unity Discussions\n    License: Not Applicable\n    Usage:
    Math logic for chunk loading iteration in a Spiral Loop.\n\n  <link=\"https://github.com/ManlyMarco/FPSCounter\"><u><b>FPSCounter</b></u></link>
    by ManlyMarco\n    License: Apache 2.0\n    Usage: Implementation reference for
    the 'PerformanceMonitor' dual-hook 'Stopwatch' architecture and per-phase CPU
    timing methodology."
